
Aṅguttara Nikāya 1 
1. Rūpādivagga 
1 
# NOTE: This translation is meant to deliberately echo the English idiom “So I hear, so I’ve heard”. It means that it has been passed down in oral tradition.
Evaṃ me sutaṃ—
ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. 
Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: 
“bhikkhavo”ti. 
“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. 
Bhagavā etadavoca: 
“Nāhaṃ, bhikkhave, aññaṃ ekarūpampi samanupassāmi yaṃ evaṃ purisassa cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhati yathayidaṃ, bhikkhave, itthirūpaṃ. 
Itthirūpaṃ, bhikkhave, purisassa cittaṃ pariyādāya tiṭṭhatī”ti. 
Paṭhamaṃ. 
